  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Computing and Cybersecurity Teacher",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>●     Teach core and applied computing modules, with a strong focus on <strong>cybersecurity</strong> and Python programming.</p><p>●     Design learner-centred lessons that build skills in secure coding, threat analysis, and ethical hacking.</p><p>●     Guide students through real-world projects aligned with the UN Sustainable Development Goals.</p><p>●     Lead and mentor student talent through CCAs such as coding clubs, cybersecurity competitions, and SST Inc. Girls-In-Tech.</p><p>●     Lead female students in overseas education partnerships and programme.<br /></p><p><strong>Minimum Qualifications and Requirements:</strong></p><p>●     A recognised Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Cybersecurity, or a related field.</p><p>●     Proficiency in cybersecurity concepts (secure systems, threat mitigation, ethical hacking) and Python programming.</p><p>●     Strong classroom facilitation skills and a commitment to applied, inquiry-based learning.</p><p>●     Openness to overseas travel for collaborative student programmes.<br /></p><p><strong>Preferred Qualifications:</strong></p><p>●     Industry certifications such as CompTIA Security+, CEH, or CISSP.</p><p>●     Experience in curriculum design, student mentorship, or managing CCA programmes in cybersecurity or computing.</p><p>●     Familiarity with EdTech platforms, cloud tools, and innovative teaching pedagogies.<br /></p><p>We strongly encourage all candidates who are passionate advocates for inclusive technology education and supporting <strong>GIRLS-IN-STEM</strong> initiatives to apply.</p>",
